└In celebration of the life of Dean Williams
1968 - 2017
who loved Red Lion Square
He devoted his life to the struggle for socialism and a fairer world
From his family, friends and comrades"╚
┼[LEFT]
Angel
Occasionally, we are graced with the presence of an
earth bound angel. They are unable to stay with us for
long, but while they do, they bring unexpected joy
and happiness to all they touch.

[RIGHT]
Eva
07-10-2001  ~ 07-12-2003
Chasing pigeons, feeding ducks, in spite of illness 
living every moment"╦
╚Anthony Meier 1956 ~ 2012
"We know only too well that what we are doing is nothing more than a
drop in the ocean. But if the drop were not there, the ocean would he missing something". Mother Teresa"═
╩[BENCH BACK]
How do you know you're God? Simple, when I pray to him I find l'm talking to myself... THE RULING CLASS

[UNDER SEAT]
Peter Barnes, playwright, filmmaker, father and friend. 1931 - 2004"į
čIn loving memory of a very special person
Gioacchino Visaggi who fell asleep on the 30 May 2016
He will be truly missed by his wife and two daughters
whom he dedicated his entire life, and all those who were
helped by his enormous generosity
He has shown to us all to never give up fighting in our
beliefs despite all the hardships"į
čBehind this bench stood the magnificent neo-gothic red brick
building of St Paul's School from 1884 to 1968.
Celebrated Architect: Alfred Waterhouse
Boys were evacuated in WW2 and it became the HQ for 21st Army Group
commanded by former pupil General Montgomery.
The final decision to invade Normandy was taken here on 15th May 1944,
about which President Eisenhower wrote:
"During the whole of the war I attended no other
conference so packed with rank as this one."
King George VI, Prime Minister Winston Churchill, Generals Montgomery
and Eisenhower were amongst 146 present in the Lecture Theatre.
Bench presented by the Old Pauline Trust Ltd
to commemorate the 75th Anniversary of D-Day on 6th June 2019."š
ęPRESENTED BY KNIGHT FRANK AND RUTLEY
AND RECEIVED BY
THE RT. HON. THE LORD MAYOR,
COMMANDER SIR ROBIN GILLETT, BT. G.B.E.RD. D. Sc.R.N.R.
IN THE YEAR OF
HER MAJESTY QUEEN ELIZABETH'S JUBILEE
24TH MAY 1977"█
